<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ881006-0173 </DOCNO><HL> Corrections andamp; Amplifications: McDonnell Douglas Corp. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> MD </CO><TEXT>   MCDONNELL DOUGLAS CORP. said that about 200 of the 600 employees dismissed by its Information Systems division were members of the direct sales force of the division's computer system unit, and that the computer system unit will market products only through dealers. An earlier edition incorrectly said the dismissals of sales staff and the marketing decision applied to the entire Information Systems division.    (See: &quot;Business Brief: McDonnell Douglas Corp.: Information Systems Division Dismisses 600 of Its Workers&quot; -- WSJ Oct. 5, 1988)</TEXT></DOC>